        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-10T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-10T20:00:00-05:00" n="231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-11T08:00:00+07:00">April 11, 1945—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>606. We understand that Dr. Sun Fo will shortly give a broadcast to the United
                    States, the chief purpose of which will be to convey <pb facs="0339" n="329" xml:id="pg_329"/> assurances, prior to the convening of the San Francisco
                    Conference, that there will be no civil war in China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
